{"title_page": "Deep Knowledge Ventures", "text_new": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the issue is settled -->\n{{AfDM|page=Deep Knowledge Ventures (2nd nomination)|year=2020|month=April|day=19|substed=yes|origtag=afdx|help=off}}\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Deep Knowledge Ventures \u05e8\u05e7 \u05d1\u05d9\u05d1\u05d9\n| logo = \n| logo_size = \n| type = \n| industry = [[Venture capital]]\n| fate = \n| predecessor = <!-- or: | predecessors = -->\n| successor = <!-- or: | successors = -->\n| founded = <!-- if known: {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} in [[city]], [[state]], [[country]] -->\n| founder = Dmitry Kaminskiy, co-founder\n| defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| hq_location_city = [[Hong Kong]]\n| hq_location_country = \n| area_served = <!-- or: | areas_served = -->\n| key_people = \n| products = \n| owner = <!-- or: | owners = -->\n| num_employees = \n| num_employees_year = <!-- Year of num_employees data (if known) -->\n| parent = \n| website = {{URL|https://www.dkv.global/}}\n}}\n'''Deep Knowledge Ventures''' is a [[venture capital]] firm based in [[Hong Kong]] with an office in [[London]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.deepknowledgeventures.com/|title=DKV|website=www.deepknowledgeventures.com|accessdate=2 November 2016}}<br>- {{Cite web|url=http://dkv.pandn.xyz/|title=Deep Knowledge Ventures|website=dkv.pandn.xyz|accessdate=2 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103234133/http://dkv.pandn.xyz/|archive-date=3 November 2016|url-status=dead}}<br>- {{Cite news|url=https://www.cbinsights.com/investor/deep-knowledge-ventures|title=Deep Knowledge Ventures&nbsp;\u2014 CB Insights|accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref>{{Self-published source|date=April 2020|reason=The corporate website doesn't provide any physical address of the company, phone numbers, or emails. The only evidence provided in their own website that prove this capital venture is real and not an empty corporate shell is a linkidin page.}} The fund primarily invests in [[Health care|healthcare]], [[artificial intelligence]], [[big data]] and [[Financial technology|fintech]].\n\nDKV's portfolio included Transplanetary, a Silicon Valley-based space development company that aimed to make the global space sector more accessible and attractive.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20140910006205/en/Deep-Knowledge-Ventures-Investment-Space|title=Deep Knowledge Ventures Makes First Investment in Space |website=Business Wire|accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nPart of Transplanetary's activities included SPOCK (Space Program Ontologically Computed Knowledge),{{Better source needed example|date=April 2020|reason=A \"transplanetary\" corporation with a program called SPOCK?  I didn't find any reliable source but it seems a joke.|importance=}}<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://blog.executivebiz.com/2014/09/deep-knowledge-ventures-to-fund-transplanetary-for-ai-space-program/|title=Deep Knowledge Ventures to Fund Transplanetary for AI, Space Program|newspaper=ExecutiveBiz|accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref> a machine learning program able to use real-time analysis of trends in the space industry to make investment recommendations. The system was aimed at analyzing publicly available data on commercial space companies, government space agencies, NGOs and academic research labs. The dataset created by SPOCK should have helped space exploration and settlement, by enabling investors to identify optimum investment targets, analysts to monitor industry growth and industry professionals to target supply chain partners.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://oemcapital.com/2014/09/deep-knowledge-ventures-acquired-transplanetary-corporation/|title=Deep Knowledge Ventures acquired Transplanetary Corporation |newspaper=Technology Investment Banking|accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref> \n\nIn 2015, Deep Knowledge Ventures incorporated a subsidiary investment fund, Deep Knowledge Life Sciences (DKLS), a London-based venture fund focused on disruptive [[biopharmaceutical]], [[Precision medicine|precision medicin]]<nowiki/>e, and AI healthcare companies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.deepknowledge.life/|title=DeepKnowledge.Life Sciences|website=www.deepknowledge.life|accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nDKLS's portfolio companies including [[Insilico Medicine]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://insilicomedicine.com/|title=Insilico Medicine|website=insilicomedicine.com|accessdate=2 November 2016}}<br>- {{Cite news|url=https://globenewswire.com/news-release/2015/07/13/751621/10141467/en/Insilico-Medicine-Inc-to-Utilize-Deep-Learning-for-Drug-Repurposing-and-Discovery-in-Cancer-and-Age-Related-Diseases.html|title=Insilico Medicine, Inc. to Utilize Deep Learning for Drug Repurposing and Discovery in Cancer and Age-Related Diseases|last=Inc.|first=InSilico Medicine|newspaper=GlobeNewswire News Room|accessdate=2 November 2016}}<br>- {{Cite news|url=https://www.genomeweb.com/informatics/silico-medicine-opens-us-office-prepares-launch-drug-discovery-software-aging-re|title=InSilico Medicine Opens US Office, Prepares to Launch Drug Discovery Software for Aging Research Market|newspaper=GenomeWeb|accessdate=2 November 2016}}<br>- {{Cite news|url=http://www.news-medical.net/news/20160622/Insilico-Medicine-collaborates-with-Asia-Genomics-to-develop-advanced-personalized-longevity-suite.aspx|title=Insilico Medicine collaborates with Asia Genomics to develop advanced personalized longevity suite|date=22 June 2016|newspaper=News-Medical.net|accessdate=2 November 2016}}<br>- {{Cite news|url=http://www.streetinsider.com/Press+Releases/Deep+Knowledge+Ventures+Flagship+Investment+Insilico+Medicine+Finalist+at+GPU+Tech+Conference/10372458.html|title=Deep Knowledge Ventures Flagship Investment Insilico Medicine Finalist at GPU Tech Conference|newspaper=StreetInsider.com|accessdate=2 November 2016}}<br>- {{Cite web|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/2